folder: Washington Street & Jane Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Washington Street, north from south of Jane Street. A section of the future elevated roadbed for freight trains has already been built on the west side of the street from Horatio to Gansevoort Streets, where a warehouse is to be built over it.

March 12, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Washington Street & Jane Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Washington Street, west side, north from Jane Street, during the demolition of the old buildings.

September 24, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same scene, three and a half years later. A new warehouse is being built over and including the elevated roadbed in the block from Horatio to Gansevoort Streets.

April 9, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
